# Testing Patterns

## Test Structure (AAA)

```ts
describe('UserService', () => {
  it('should create a user with hashed password', async () => {
    // Arrange
    const input = { email: 'test@test.com', password: 'plain' };
    // Act
    const user = await userService.create(input);
    // Assert
    expect(user.email).toBe(input.email);
    expect(user.password).not.toBe(input.password);
  });
});
```

## Mocking Modules

```ts
jest.mock('../db', () => ({
  users: { findUnique: jest.fn(), create: jest.fn() },
}));

beforeEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks());
```

## Test Data Factories

```ts
function makeUser(overrides: Partial<User> = {}): User {
  return { id: 'u1', email: 'test@test.com', role: 'user', ...overrides };
}
```

## Integration Tests with Supertest

```ts
const app = createApp();
describe('POST /api/users', () => {
  it('returns 201 on valid input', async () => {
    const res = await request(app).post('/api/users').send({ email: 'a@b.com', password: 'pass' });
    expect(res.status).toBe(201);
    expect(res.body.email).toBe('a@b.com');
  });
});
```

## Rules
- Test behavior, not implementation
- One assertion per test (when possible)
- `beforeEach` / `afterEach` for setup/teardown, not `beforeAll`
- Name tests as: 'should [behavior] when [condition]'

