# Error Handling

## Result Type

```ts
type Ok<T> = { ok: true; value: T };
type Err = { ok: false; error: string; code?: string };
type Result<T> = Ok<T> | Err;

const ok = <T>(value: T): Ok<T> => ({ ok: true, value });
const err = (error: string, code?: string): Err => ({ ok: false, error, code });
```

## Typed Application Errors

```ts
class AppError extends Error {
  constructor(public message: string, public statusCode: number, public code: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'AppError';
  }
}

class NotFoundError extends AppError {
  constructor(resource: string) { super(`${resource} not found`, 404, 'NOT_FOUND'); }
}
class ValidationError extends AppError {
  constructor(message: string) { super(message, 400, 'VALIDATION_ERROR'); }
}
```

## Express Error Middleware

```ts
app.use((err: Error, req: Request, res: Response, _next: NextFunction) => {
  if (err instanceof AppError) {
    return res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message, code: err.code });
  }
  console.error(err); // log unexpected errors
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});
```

## Rules
- Never swallow errors silently (`catch {}` is forbidden)
- Always log unexpected errors with stack trace
- Return typed errors from service layer, throw in route handlers
- `finally` for cleanup (db connections, temp files)

